---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon";
import { Picture } from "@astrojs/image/components";

const skillSet = [
  {
    name: "HTML",
  },
  {
    name: "CSS",
  },
  {
    name: "Javascript",
  },
  {
    name: "TailwindCss",
  },
  {
    name: "Astro",
  },
  {
    name: "Typescript",
  },
];
---

<div class="prose">
  <article class="text-black">
    <h1 class="text-4xl underline text-center">Pearl China</h1>
    <Picture
      class="mb-8 rounded-xl shadow-md"
      src="/images/PearlChina.png"
      widths={[400, 600, 1024]}
      sizes="(max-width: 400px) 370px, (max-width: 600px) 600px, 1024px"
      aspectRatio="5:3"
      alt="Pearl China"
      format="png"
      background="white"
    />
    <div class="flex">
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="HTML" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="CSS" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="Javascript" />
      <a href="https://pearlchina.co.uk/" target="_blank">
        <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="External" />
      </a>
    </div>
    <p>
      My first site that I deployed online was for a local business. It was a simple
      site that used some vanilla Javascript and had a Google Map embed in it.
      It is hosted on CloudFlare and gets a humble 700 vists a week.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="text-black mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl underline text-center">Blog Site / Portfolio</h1>
    <Picture
      class="mb-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg"
      src="/images/Portfolio.png"
      widths={[400, 600, 1024]}
      sizes="(max-width: 400px) 370px, (max-width: 600px) 600px, 1024px"
      aspectRatio="5:3"
      alt="Front End Portfolio"
      format="png"
      background="white"
    />
    <div class="flex">
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="HTML" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="Javascript" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="Typescript" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="Astro" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="TailwindCss" />
    </div>
    <p>
      My revamped portfolio site. My initial <a href="https://expressowl.github.io/Frontend-Portfolio/" class='hover:text-blue-500' >one</a>  had nice colors (in my
      opinion), but did not have the scalability of my current one that was made
      with Astro. I also wanted to challenge myself and use all the tech that I
      have learnt so far.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="text-black">
    <h1 class="text-4xl underline text-center">Initial Speed</h1>
    <Picture
      class="mb-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg"
      src="/images/InitialSpeed.png"
      widths={[400, 600, 1024]}
      sizes="(max-width: 400px) 370px, (max-width: 600px) 600px, 1024px"
      aspectRatio="1:2"
      alt="Initial Speed"
      format="png"
      background="white"
    />
    <div class="flex">
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="HTML" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="Javascript" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="TailwindCss" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="Vite" />
      <a href="https://tailwind-website.onrender.com/" target="_blank">
        <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="External" />
      </a>
    </div>
    <p>
      A Mock up site for my friend's Skyline repair business. This was made with
      mobile in mind first and taught me the problems of having high quality
      images. They may look sweet but they take FOREVER to load if your user has
      a slow internet connection. I learnt about lazy loading and to adjust
      width and height of images so that you don't load more than you need to.
    </p>
  </article>
</div>

<section class="prose text-black py-4 border-b last:border-t">
  <h1 class="text-4xl underline text-center mb-4">More Projects</h1>

  <div class="text-center">
    <a
      href="https://github.com/ExpressOwl"
      target="_blank"
      class="inline-block m-auto text-center text-3xl bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 to-pink-500 px-2 py-4 cursor-pointer transition-all hover:shadow-md"
      >Visit my GitHub</a
    >
  </div>

  <p>
    If you visit my GitHub you can see some of the more mundane projects, such
    as creating a toast message, making a pomodoro timer and making a ReactJS
    countdown app.
  </p>
</section>
